reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Exactly what I paid for and expected, but description may be misleading
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I bought this ring so that I could wear it for a few weeks and be able to adjust the size to find the right size to use to resize my wedding ring. It was perfect for this purpose, and that’s why I bought a ring that was only $13.That said, I feel like I should just alert others to the fact that these “14K Gold, long lasting finish” rings are only $13. For the ring to be so cheap, the gold plating must be extremely thin. This was, of course, true, and the rose gold color started to rub off within about 2 weeks of daily wear. Now I’ve had it for about a month, and the front is mostly silver, the back is mostly silver, and the sides as well. In addition, whatever metal is underneath is very soft, and so it also has a bunch of scratches and therefore looks dull, especially on the side facing my palm (where it obviously comes into contact with things I hold in my hands).Again, I knew what I was buying: a temporary ring to wear for a few weeks that I could adjust larger and smaller to determine a size that won’t give my finger a rash or an indentation, so that I don’t have to keep paying real money to resize my real wedding ring. Just don’t buy this ring thinking you are getting some amazing deal on a real, lasting 14K gold ring.The reason I am giving only 3 stars is that I feel that the description stating that the 14k gold is a “long lasting finish” is false advertising. I guess “long lasting” is subjective, but I feel like any reasonable person would assume long lasting means you can wear it for at least a season. This should really be advertised as temporary costume jewelry. If you only wore it for special nights, it would probably last much longer. I do see a 60 day guarantee, so I’m sure one could try and use that, but again, I felt I got my use out of the ring. Would I have liked it to stay looking nice so I could keep wearing it on another finger? Of course! But I got my $13 worth.On the plus side, they were very honest that the ring is hypoallergenic and I’m guessing it truly was nickel and lead free. I have very sensitive skin (part of the reason for needing a larger ring size) and it has never bothered my skin the way a nickel ring would. The packaging was very nice and pretty, and the ring itself looks lovely when you first get it!
